quran[20]{c,v,t}:
  90,1,I swear (or call to witness) this City (Mecca)
  90,2,And you (Muhammad) are a dweller of this City
  90,3,And the (mystic ties) of Parent and Child
  90,4,"We have surely created man in suffering (struggle, trouble, sorrow)"
  90,5,Does he think that none has power over him
  90,6,"He says, \"I have squandered wealth in plenty"
  90,7,Does he think that no one sees him
  90,8,Have We not made for him two eyes
  90,9,"And a tongue, and two lips"
  90,10,And guided him in the two highways
  90,11,But he has not attempted the ascent
  90,12,And what will explain to you the ascent
  90,13,"It is freeing captives (or prisoners, slaves, the restricted or bound)"
  90,14,Or feeding on the day of privation
  90,15,An orphan who is a kin
  90,16,Or a destitute lying in the dust (of misery)
  90,17,"And again (it is) to be of those who believe and encourage each other to patience, and encourage each other to mercy"
  90,18,These are the fellows of the right
  90,19,"But those who disbelieve in our signs, they are the fellows of the left"
  90,20,For them is the enclosing Fire